subject:

TWO ROADS (review the book or Psalms)
===================================================================
verse:

Let everything that lives sing praises to the Lord Praise
the Lord! (Ps. 150:6)

===================================================================
reflection:

If you feel like treasure hunting go back and review the
psalms, in doing this you will discover the parallels of our
journey through life. It begins with presenting us two
roads: the way to life and the way to death. If we choose
God’s way to life, we will still face both blessings and
troubles, joy and grief, success and obstacles. But
throughout it all, God is at our side, guiding, encouraging,
comforting, and caring. Knowing this should cause us to
praise God for leading us in the right direction and for
assuring us of a place in the perfect world He has in store
for those who have faithfully followed Him.

===================================================================
prayer:

Heavenly Father, thank You for guiding us on the journey of
life, showing us the two roads-the way of life and the way
of death. Help us to choose Your path, trusting in Your
presence through blessings and hardships alike. Comfort and
encourage us with the assurance of Your care and the promise
of eternal life with You. May we praise You continually for
leading us safely home. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
